{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SbbfcyuRbrtS32M2p7Ar2d","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-1: Create AgentDriver Interface and Types\n     2→\n     3→## Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer,\n    12→I want an `AgentDriver` interface that abstracts agent execution,\n    13→So that Ralph can be replaced or supplemented without touching 28 files.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given `src/lib/agents/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it exports `AgentDriver`, `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given the `AgentDriver` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `readonly name: string`, `spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess`, `parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null`, `getStatusFile(): string` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given the `SpawnOpts` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `storyKey: string`, `prompt: string`, `workDir: string`, `timeout: number`, `env?: Record<string, string>` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given the `AgentProcess` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `stdout: Readable`, `stderr: Readable`, `on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void`, `kill(signal?: string): void` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given the `AgentEvent` type, when inspected, then it is a discriminated union on `type` covering: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given `src/lib/agents/index.ts` exists, when inspected, then it re-exports all types from `./types.js` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given no file in `src/lib/agents/`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` exists, when inspected, then it verifies the type exports are importable and the `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→\n    28→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    29→\n    30→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5): Create `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n    31→  - [x] Define and export `SpawnOpts` interface with `storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env?`\n    32→  - [x] Import `Readable` from `node:stream`\n    33→  - [x] Define and export `AgentProcess` interface with `stdout`, `stderr`, `on('close')`, `kill()`\n    34→  - [x] Define and export `AgentEvent` discriminated union type with all 8 event types\n    35→  - [x] Define and export `AgentDriver` interface with `name`, `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`\n    36→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 6): Create `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n    37→  - [x] Re-export all types from `./types.js`\n    38→  - [x] Add placeholder comment for future driver registry and implementations\n    39→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 10): Create `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`\n    40→  - [x] Verify all type exports are importable from the module\n    41→  - [x] Verify `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types via type-level tests\n    42→  - [x] Verify `AgentDriver` interface shape matches specification\n    43→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 7): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    44→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 8): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    45→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 9): Verify all new files are under 300 lines\n    46→\n    47→## Dev Notes\n    48→\n    49→### Architecture Compliance\n    50→\n    51→- **Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction):** This story creates the foundational types from architecture-v3.md Decision 3. The `AgentDriver` interface is the contract that `RalphDriver` (story 13-2) and future drivers must implement.\n    52→- **Decision 4 (Domain Subdirectories):** Files go under `src/lib/agents/` per the architecture's target file tree.\n    53→- **300-line limit (Decision 7, NFR5):** All new files must stay under 300 lines. This is a types-only story so files will be well under the limit.\n    54→\n    55→### Implementation Guidance\n    56→\n    57→This is a **types-only story**. No implementation code beyond interface definitions and the `index.ts` re-export facade.\n    58→\n    59→The `AgentProcess` interface wraps Node.js `ChildProcess` but abstracts it so future drivers (direct API calls, WebSocket connections) can implement it differently. Import `Readable` from `node:stream` for the stream types.\n    60→\n    61→`AgentEvent` is a discriminated union on `type`. The `parseOutput()` method converts raw agent output lines into typed events. Each driver knows its own output format.\n    62→\n    63→All types should be `export`ed (not `export default`) so they can be individually imported.\n    64→\n    65→### Type Design Notes\n    66→\n    67→```typescript\n    68→// src/lib/agents/types.ts\n    69→import type { Readable } from 'node:stream';\n    70→\n    71→export interface SpawnOpts {\n    72→  storyKey: string;\n    73→  prompt: string;\n    74→  workDir: string;\n    75→  timeout: number;\n    76→  env?: Record<string, string>;\n    77→}\n    78→\n    79→export interface AgentProcess {\n    80→  stdout: Readable;"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3ce6f3e2-c583-4074-ab3d-bf1fc6d87b66","uuid":"0929aa51-48bd-4a4d-af99-97ae13a2aef5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:38:00.839Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types.md","content":"# Story 13-1: Create AgentDriver Interface and Types\n\n## Status: review\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want an `AgentDriver` interface that abstracts agent execution,\nSo that Ralph can be replaced or supplemented without touching 28 files.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. Given `src/lib/agents/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it exports `AgentDriver`, `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n2. Given the `AgentDriver` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `readonly name: string`, `spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess`, `parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null`, `getStatusFile(): string` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n3. Given the `SpawnOpts` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `storyKey: string`, `prompt: string`, `workDir: string`, `timeout: number`, `env?: Record<string, string>` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n4. Given the `AgentProcess` interface, when inspected, then it defines: `stdout: Readable`, `stderr: Readable`, `on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void`, `kill(signal?: string): void` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n5. Given the `AgentEvent` type, when inspected, then it is a discriminated union on `type` covering: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n6. Given `src/lib/agents/index.ts` exists, when inspected, then it re-exports all types from `./types.js` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n7. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n8. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n9. Given no file in `src/lib/agents/`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n10. Given `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` exists, when inspected, then it verifies the type exports are importable and the `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5): Create `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n  - [x] Define and export `SpawnOpts` interface with `storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env?`\n  - [x] Import `Readable` from `node:stream`\n  - [x] Define and export `AgentProcess` interface with `stdout`, `stderr`, `on('close')`, `kill()`\n  - [x] Define and export `AgentEvent` discriminated union type with all 8 event types\n  - [x] Define and export `AgentDriver` interface with `name`, `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`\n- [x] Task 2 (AC: 6): Create `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n  - [x] Re-export all types from `./types.js`\n  - [x] Add placeholder comment for future driver registry and implementations\n- [x] Task 3 (AC: 10): Create `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`\n  - [x] Verify all type exports are importable from the module\n  - [x] Verify `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers all 8 event types via type-level tests\n  - [x] Verify `AgentDriver` interface shape matches specification\n- [x] Task 4 (AC: 7): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n- [x] Task 5 (AC: 8): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n- [x] Task 6 (AC: 9): Verify all new files are under 300 lines\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture Compliance\n\n- **Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction):** This story creates the foundational types from architecture-v3.md Decision 3. The `AgentDriver` interface is the contract that `RalphDriver` (story 13-2) and future drivers must implement.\n- **Decision 4 (Domain Subdirectories):** Files go under `src/lib/agents/` per the architecture's target file tree.\n- **300-line limit (Decision 7, NFR5):** All new files must stay under 300 lines. This is a types-only story so files will be well under the limit.\n\n### Implementation Guidance\n\nThis is a **types-only story**. No implementation code beyond interface definitions and the `index.ts` re-export facade.\n\nThe `AgentProcess` interface wraps Node.js `ChildProcess` but abstracts it so future drivers (direct API calls, WebSocket connections) can implement it differently. Import `Readable` from `node:stream` for the stream types.\n\n`AgentEvent` is a discriminated union on `type`. The `parseOutput()` method converts raw agent output lines into typed events. Each driver knows its own output format.\n\nAll types should be `export`ed (not `export default`) so they can be individually imported.\n\n### Type Design Notes\n\n```typescript\n// src/lib/agents/types.ts\nimport type { Readable } from 'node:stream';\n\nexport interface SpawnOpts {\n  storyKey: string;\n  prompt: string;\n  workDir: string;\n  timeout: number;\n  env?: Record<string, string>;\n}\n\nexport interface AgentProcess {\n  stdout: Readable;","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":164}}}
