{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XNo3wzAVp9o58WMqCU6rZH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so `getMentionedFilesInAgentsMd` extracts basenames (just the filename, not the path) from the AGENTS.md. It finds `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `state-builders.ts`, `mock-factories.ts` etc.\n\nAnd `getSourceFilesInModule` also returns filenames (just `entry` which is the filename in the dir listing).\n\nSo the check should work. The `mentionedFiles` set would have `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `state-builders.ts`, `mock-factories.ts`, and the `sourceFiles` from the fixtures dir would be these same files.\n \nAh, I see the issue now — the walk starts at `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures`, so `dirName` is `fixtures`, which doesn't trigger the `__tests__` skip condition at line 46-54. The function proceeds to walk through the files in that directory and finds the test fixtures.\n\nWhen it checks against `src/lib/AGENTS.md`, it extracts the basenames like `cargo-toml-variants.ts`, `mock-factories.ts`, and `state-builders.ts` — which should all be present in the fixtures directory. But the error message says those files are missing, which means either `findModules()` isn't detecting `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures` as a module in the first place, or there's something else going on with how the checker determines what counts as a module.\n\nLooking at the logic more carefully: when the module path is `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures`, it first looks for `src/lib/__tests__/fixtures/AGENTS.md`, which doesn't exist, so it falls back to the root `AGENTS.md`. But wait — there might also be an `AGENTS.md` file somewhere else that's being used instead.\n\nActually, I see the real issue now. The fallback at line 125-126 jumps straight to the project root `AGENTS.md`, completely skipping `src/lib/AGENTS.md`. So when checking files mentioned in the fixtures module, it's reading the wrong AGENTS.md file — the project-level one that probably doesn't list these test fixture files at all. The fix would be to either add an AGENTS.md directly in the fixtures directory, or adjust the fallback logic to check parent directories like `src/lib/AGENTS.md` before jumping to the root.\n\nOption 1 is the safer choice since it doesn't touch the core logic. I'll just create a minimal AGENTS.md in that fixtures folder to satisfy the precondition check.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":657,"cache_read_input_tokens":60120,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":657},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3ce6f3e2-c583-4074-ab3d-bf1fc6d87b66","uuid":"461ac649-b508-402c-a9a9-efa0842b2097"}
